INSTALLATION
============

1) Download the MATLAByrinth repository with the following commands:

    mkdir ~/MATLAByrinth-install
    cd ~/MATLAByrinth-install
    git clone https://github.com/davidozog/MATLAByrinth.git

2) Install mpi4py by issuing the following commands:

    cd ~/MATLAByrinth-install
    wget https://mpi4py.googlecode.com/files/mpi4py-1.3.tar.gz
    tar xzvf mpi4py-1.3.tar.gz
    cd mpi4py-1.3
    module purge
    module load python/2.7.2 numpy/1.6.1 mpi-tor/openmpi-1.4.5_gcc-4.4.6
    python setup.py build
    python setup.py install --user

3) Add the bin dir to your path.  For example in your ~/.bashrc file:
    export PATH=$PATH:~/MATLAByrinth-install/MATLABYrinth/bin

   Also set the MATLABYRINT environment variable:
    export MATLABYRINTH='~/MATLAByrinth-install/MATLAByrinth'

4) If it does not exist, create the following directory and file:
    ~/Documents/MATLAB/startup.m

  and append this line to the startup.m file:
    addpath ~/MATLAByrinth-install/MATLABYrinth/src/matlab

5) Refer to the MATLAByrinth REAME file to see how to test the installation.

